{#
  Shared page header — Wave 1 of the UI redesign (2026-06-03).
  Tool pages (Today, Deals, Merchants list, Funders, Upload, Intake,
  Review Queue) replace their inline .deck markup with this include
  during Wave 2. The dossier (merchant_detail_dossier.html.j2) keeps
  its bespoke .masthead since it carries the editorial 92px scale.

  Renders the existing .deck structure exactly — no new CSS needed
  (the `.deck` / `.deck h1` / `.deck h1 em` / `.deck .meta` /
  `.deck .actions` rules in aegis-tool.css already style this shape).
  This partial only centralizes the markup.

  Inputs (all required unless marked optional):
    title       — string, page title (becomes <h1>)
    subtitle    — string, optional em-tagged subtitle inside h1
    meta        — string, optional small-caps meta line on the right
    actions     — list of {label, href, variant?} dicts, optional;
                  variant is one of "primary" | "ghost" | None (default
                  is the existing .btn behavior — no special class)

  Example caller (Wave 2 form to adopt):
    {% include "_page_header.html.j2" with context %}
    where the calling template has set:
      {% set title = "Today" %}
      {% set subtitle = "· attention queue" %}
      {% set meta = now %}
      {% set actions = [{"label": "Upload PDF", "href": "/ui/upload",
                         "variant": "primary"}] %}
#}
<header class="deck">
  <h1>{{ title }}{% if subtitle %} <em>{{ subtitle }}</em>{% endif %}</h1>
  {% if meta %}<div class="meta">{{ meta }}</div>{% endif %}
  {% if actions %}
    <div class="actions">
      {% for a in actions %}
        <a class="btn{% if a.variant %} {{ a.variant }}{% endif %}" href="{{ a.href }}">{{ a.label }}</a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% endif %}
</header>
